prompts.frontCover:
A humorous and lighthearted watercolor illustration for a birthday card front cover. The scene features cartoon versions of a younger woman and an older woman (Lao Lao), based on the reference photo. Lao Lao is on the left, depicted as a charming cartoon character with short, neat gray hair, gentle wrinkles, and glasses, wearing a light gray floral top with a white cardigan over it. She is shown in a comical pose, playfully flexing one bicep with a wide, mischievous grin, as if showing off her youthful energy. The younger woman, on the right, has long dark hair, and is wearing a white V-neck t-shirt. She is reacting with a look of loving amusement and surprise, with wide eyes and an open-mouthed smile, perhaps clapping or gesturing towards Lao Lao in admiration. The background is a simple, soft wash of cheerful pastel colors like pale yellow, soft pink, and light teal, with artistic paint splatters and organic bleeds creating a festive and joyful atmosphere.

In the center of the card, written in a beautiful, readable, and elegant handwritten cursive script, is the text: "Happy Birthday, Lao Lao! Still the strongest of us all!" The entire artwork is in a flat 2D watercolor style, with soft, flowing colors, visible brush strokes, and a subtle paper texture.

- Reference photos provided for character creation
- Characters should only appear on the front cover
- Transform real people into artistic cartoon/illustrated versions matching the style
- Maintain recognizable features while adapting to the artistic style
